dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104arl1665702601386.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/arl1665702601386.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/arl1665702601386.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"arl1665702601386\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n $formdbmod (deprecated)\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"arl1665702601386___formdbmoddeprecated__266796\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the modification status of database fields in the current Form.\n </p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"arl1665702601386__note_w158ab1b7b3_w159ab1b7_w160ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formdbmod</span>\n         function is deprecated. It has been superseded by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$instancedbmod</span>, which\n         is applicable to all component types. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"len1665702601301.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/len1665702601301.html\" title=\"Return the modification status of database fields in the current component instance.\">$instancedbmod</a>. </div>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"arl1665702601386__topic_d83894e1_d83895e1_d83896e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arl1665702601386__p_d83897e1_d83898e1_d83899e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Return</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formdbmod</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"arl1665702601386__topic_d55492e1_d55493e1_d55494e1_d55495e1_d55496e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1181696e88\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"arl1665702601386__table_d8678e1_d8679e1_d8680e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values Returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formdbmod</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"arl1665702601386__table_d8678e1_d8679e1_d8680e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"arl1665702601386__table_d8678e1_d8679e1_d8680e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Meaning</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"arl1665702601386__table_d8678e1_d8679e1_d8680e1__entry__1\">\n 0\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"arl1665702601386__table_d8678e1_d8679e1_d8680e1__entry__2\">\n Field has not been modified; this can be because:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"arl1665702601386__li_d34364e1_d34365e1_d34366e1\">No database field has been\n                              modified. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"arl1665702601386__li_d34367e1_d34368e1_d34369e1\">No database occurrences have been\n                              added or removed. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"arl1665702601386__li_d34370e1_d34371e1_d34372e1\">No entities are painted on the\n                              form. </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"arl1665702601386__table_d8678e1_d8679e1_d8680e1__entry__1\">\n 1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"arl1665702601386__table_d8678e1_d8679e1_d8680e1__entry__2\">\n Field has been modified; this can be due to:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"arl1665702601386__li_d34373e1_d34374e1_d34375e1\">A database field in a database\n                              entity has been modified. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"arl1665702601386__li_d34376e1_d34377e1_d34378e1\">An database occurrence has been\n                              added to or removed from the component. </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"arl1665702601386__topic_d55497e1_d55498e1_d55499e1_d55500e1_d55501e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1181696e167\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arl1665702601386__d5909e20\">Use in Form components.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"arl1665702601386__topic_d55502e1_d55503e1_d55504e1_d55505e1_d55506e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1181696e177\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arl1665702601386__p_d83912e1_d83913e1_d83914e1\">Use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formdbmod</span> to test whether any database field has been modified. Non-database fields (<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Is external</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=false</code>) do not affect <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formdbmod</span>. The value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formdbmod</span> is actually the inclusive logical OR of the values of the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldmod</span> function for all database fields in the form.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"arl1665702601386__p_d83915e1_d83916e1_d83917e1\">Statements that affect the value of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$formdbmod</span> are the same as those that affect <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$instancedbmod</span>, and the return values are determined in the same way.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/len1665702601301.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$instancedbmod</a><p>Return the modification status of database fields in the current component instance.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525849\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525849\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$formdbmod (deprecated) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 27, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $formdbmod (deprecated) Return the modification status of database fields in the current Form. Note: The $formdbmod function is deprecated. It has been superseded by $instancedbmod , which is applicable to all component types. For more information, see $instancedbmod . Return = $formdbmod Return Values Table 1. Values Returned in $formdbmod Value Meaning 0 Field has not been modified; this can be because: No database field has been modified. No database occurrences have been added or removed. No entities are painted on the form. 1 Field has been modified; this can be due to: A database field in a database entity has been modified. An database occurrence has been added to or removed from the component. Use Use in Form components. Description Use $formdbmod to test whether any database field has been modified. Non-database fields ( Is external =false ) do not affect $formdbmod . The value of $formdbmod is actually the inclusive logical OR of the values of the $fieldmod function for all database fields in the form. Statements that affect the value of $formdbmod are the same as those that affect $instancedbmod , and the return values are determined in the same way. Related Links $instancedbmod Return the modification status of database fields in the current component instance. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}